```java
Document doc = new Document(&quot;https://example.com/&quot;);
Element script = doc.head().appendElement(&quot;script&quot;);
script.text(&quot;var i=0;if(i&lt;5){alert(123);}&quot;);
System.out.println(doc.html());
```

produces:

```html
&lt;html&gt;
 &lt;head&gt;
  &lt;script&gt;var i=0;if(i&lt;5){alert(123);}&lt;/script&gt;
 &lt;/head&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
```

This was implemented in this [commit][2] and has been in jsoup since 1.14.1 (we&#39;re on 1.15.3 as of writing).


  [1]: https://jsoup.org/apidocs/org/jsoup/nodes/Element.html#text(java.lang.String)
  [2]: https://github.com/jhy/jsoup/commit/724b2c5bf576cbd548738756bfe5f7a7b90c6239

Just to be sure that the content of every script element is unescaped, I execute a cleanup just before exporting the Document. It transfers text of a script element into a DataNode:

		Elements scriptElements = document.getElementsByTag(&quot;script&quot;);
		if (scriptElements != null) {
			Iterator&lt;Element&gt; scriptIterator = scriptElements.iterator();
			while (scriptIterator.hasNext()) {
				Element script = scriptIterator.next();
				String data = script.data();
				String text = script.text();
				script.text(&quot;&quot;);
				script.appendChild(new DataNode((text != null ? text : &quot;&quot;) + (text != null &amp;&amp; data != null ? &quot; &quot; : &quot;&quot;)
						+ (data != null ? data : &quot;&quot;)));
			}
		}

